INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '065e1955-1830-4811-9e99-67b5d105292c',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$SvelteKit Testing — Isolate Loaders & Actions, Then Verify Full Flows with Playwright$escape$,
  $escape$SvelteKit's `load` functions and form actions are pure-ish functions — test them directly without spinning up a server. Import your `+page.server.ts` loader and call it with a mock `RequestEvent`. Assert on the returned data shape. For actions, call the named export (e.g. `actions.default`) with a fake `request` containing `FormData`. No `fetch` mocking ceremony needed for most cases — just construct the event object.

For full route integration, Playwright's `page.goto('/dashboard')` exercises the actual SvelteKit router, SSR, and hydration. Use `page.waitForSelector` after navigation to assert hydrated state, not just SSR HTML. For authenticated routes, seed cookies via `context.addCookies` before the test — Clerk or any JWT-based session can be injected this way.

Combine both layers: unit tests catch broken loader logic fast; Playwright catches broken routing, redirects (`throw redirect(302, '/login')`), and form action side-effects that only surface end-to-end. Skip testing `+layout.server.ts` in isolation unless it contains non-trivial logic — the E2E layer covers it implicitly.$escape$,
  $escape$// +page.server.test.ts
import { load, actions } from './+page.server';
import { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest';

describe('dashboard loader', () => {
  it('returns user data for authenticated event', async () => {
    const event = {
      locals: { user: { id: '42', role: 'admin' } },
      url: new URL('http://localhost/dashboard'),
    } as any;

    const result = await load(event);
    expect(result.user.role).toBe('admin');
  });

  it('action rejects empty form submission', async () => {
    const formData = new FormData();
    const request = new Request('http://localhost', { method: 'POST', body: formData });
    const response = await actions.default({ request } as any);
    expect(response?.status).toBe(400);
  });
});$escape$,
